General Description images tree contains the relationship among a set of images and it does by defining a map of maps data structure following the next rules:
 Images tree is defined in a YAML structure. The main key that contains the tree definition is named images_tree, which value is a map of maps data structure. Under images_tree are placed all the images' names that belong to images tree. Image&rsquo;s name is the first level keys. The second level keys identifies the image versions and are placed under each image name key. Image version&rsquo;s value is the image definition for that specific version.  In case an image name or image version contains a . (dot), it is needed to quote it to avoid the yaml parser to fails.   Example  On that example you could see such as image&rsquo;s names key ubuntu, php-fpm and php-cli. Taking a look to ubuntu image, you could see the versions 18.04 and 20.04.
